Frameworks</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Humberstone, Lloyd, 1995, &ldquo;Negation by Iteration&rdquo;,
<em>Theoria</em>, 61: 1&ndash;24.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1998, &ldquo;Many-Valued Logics,
Philosophical Issues in&rdquo;, <em>Routledge Encyclopedia of
Philosophy, Vol. 6</em>, E. Craig (ed.), Routledge: London,
pp.&nbsp;84&ndash;91.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, &ldquo;Parts and Partitions&rdquo;,
<em>Theoria</em>, 66: 41&ndash;82.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2002, &ldquo;The Modal Logic of Agreement
and Noncontingency&rdquo;, <em>Notre Dame Journal of Formal
Logic</em>, 43: 95&ndash;127.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, <em>The Connectives</em>, Cambridge
MA: MIT Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013, &ldquo;Logical Relations&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophical Perspectives</em>, 27: 176&ndash;230.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2014, &ldquo;Prior&rsquo;s OIC
Nonconservativity Example Revisited&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Applied
Non-Classical Logics</em>, 24: 209&ndash;235.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;B&eacute;ziau on <em>And</em>
and \(Or\)&rdquo;, in <em>The Road to Universal Logic:
Festschrift for the 50th Birthday of Jean-Yves B&eacute;ziau, Volume
I</em>, A. Koslow and A. Buchsbaum (eds.), Heidelberg:
Birkh&auml;user, pp. 283&ndash;307.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016, <em>Philosophical Applications of
Modal Logic</em>, London: College Publications.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019, &ldquo;Supervenience, Dependence,
Disjunction&rdquo;, <em>Logic and Logical Philosophy</em>, 28:
3&ndash;135.</li>

<li>Hyde, Dominic, 1997, &ldquo;From Heaps and Gaps to Heaps of
Gluts&rdquo;, <em>Mind</em>, 106: 641&ndash;60.</li>

<li>Jankov, V.A., 1969, &ldquo;Conjunctively Indecomposable Formulas
in Propositional Calculi&rdquo;, <em>Math. USSR&mdash;Izvestija</em>,
3: 17&ndash;35.</li>

<li>Kaminski, M. 1988, &ldquo;Nonstandard Connectives of
