<div id="acknowledgments">

<h3>Acknowledgments</h3>

<p>
I am grateful to Thomas Hendrey for drawing my attention (in 2011) to
an error in the initial version of this entry, at a point in Section 2
after the formulation of the rules \((\wedge\)I) and \((\wedge\)E), where the
discussion included the following: &ldquo;Typically \(\vdash\) will also
be determined by many further classes of valuations (meaning: other
than the class Val\((\vdash)\) of all valuations consistent with
\(\vdash)\), various subsets of Val\((\vdash)\), but not so, as just
remarked, in the present case.&rdquo; By &ldquo;the present
case&rdquo; was meant the case of \(\vdash = \vdash_{\wedge}\).
As Hendrey pointed out, this consequence relation is determined by
numerous proper subsets of the set of all \(\wedge\)-Boolean valuations, so
the claim is false. In a moment of inattention I had confusingly
passed from the correct thought that the only valuations consistent
with \(\vdash_{\wedge}\) are the \(\wedge\)-Boolean ones to the faulty
conclusion that the only class of valuations determining
\(\vdash_{\wedge}\) is the class of all \(\wedge\)-Boolean valuations.
(Many counterexamples could be given to this latter claim but one
offered by Hendrey is particularly interesting: the class of all those
\(\wedge\)-Boolean valuations with the further property that they make at
most one sentence letter false.) The reference to subsets of
Val\((\vdash)\) was ill-conceived, since the point of contrast with,
e.g., \(\vdash_{\vee}\), taken as the consequence relation (on
the language with sole connective \(\vee)\) determined by the class of all
\(\vee\)-Boolean valuations is also determined by classes of valuations
which are <em>not</em> subsets of this class since we can include also
conjunctive combinations of \(\vee\)-Boolean valuations. By contrast,
\(\vdash_{\wedge}\) can only be determined by classes of
valuations all of which are \(\wedge\)-Boolean.</p>

<script type="text/javascript" src="local.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="../../mjax/tex-chtml-full.js"></script>
</div>




